          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for consultation and study and is a short philosophical treatise considered a summary or essence (sāra) of Vedic knowledge from an Advaita (non-dualism) Vedānta perspective. Presented as a discourse between the Hindu deities Śiva and Pārvatī.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Vedāntasāra</title>
              <author>Sadānanda Yogīndra</author>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName>Vināyaka (Son of Kṛṣṇa)</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīmatparivrājakācāryaviracito sadānaṃdaviracito vedāṃtasāraḥ samāptaḥ // śrīhanumallekṣmaṇasametaḥ śrīsītārāmacaṃdraḥ jñānadātāprīyatāṃ // śake 1721 siddhā[??] saṃvatsare māghaśuddhramatipadiravivāsare sahasrabudhyupāvhakṛṣṇātmajavināyakenalikhitaṃ svāthaṃ parārthaṃ ca // śubhaṃbhūyāllekhakādhyetroḥ // (f. 11v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
